In this op-ed, Secretary of Energy Steven Chu and Secretary of Labor Hilda Solis discuss the importance of building the American clean energy economy. They highlight the need to address the energy crisis, reduce dependence on foreign oil, and combat pollution. They emphasize that investing in clean energy technologies and creating green jobs will not only benefit the economy but also protect the environment and enhance national security. They also stress the importance of cracking down on corporations that pollute and taking action against global warming. The secretaries acknowledge the challenges ahead but express the commitment of the Obama administration to create a clean energy policy that benefits all Americans.